description:
Roles & Responsibilities
With award-winning mobile banking apps and trading systems, our technology platforms help Bank deliver best-in-class products to clients. Naturally, we make sure that the phones work, emails are delivered and PCs run - but we also develop innovative collaboration platforms and workspaces that help our people share their knowledge, their expertise and their passion for our business.

Developments in technology are changing the way we communicate, work and even think. Join us here, and you'll constantly be looking ahead. We'll look to you to capitalize on new technological trends that can reshape our business and deliver value for our clients, whilst still meeting the demands of customers, regulators and the markets.

Project goal is to decomins existing platform and create a new payment platform using new technologies:

Technology stack includes Java 11, Spring, Oracle DB, Kafka, Solace JMS, Apache Tomcat, Web services, , HTML5, Node.js, Git, Python, JIRA, Confluence, Jenkins / TeamCity, Docker / Kubernetes, SDLC, Sonar, Geneos

Payments is a core product for Cash Management and one of the growth areas in Bank’s strategy. In order to support the growth ambitions and to remain a leading global player in the competitive payments market, significant investment in the payment infrastructure of Bank is applied.
The team is delivering set of key applications in Payment integration platform which are single entry point for all payments not only in Corporate Bank but across the entire Enterprise. Monthly processing volume of the applications is over €100 Billion of payment transactions across 42 countries from Europe, APAC and Americas.
As a Senior Site Reliability Engineer (m/f/x) you will be responsible for providing the DevOps function delivering the required target state and availability for the infrastructure, working closely with Development Team, L2/3 Support Team, and peer DevOps and Site Reliability Engineer teams
Responsibilities:- CI/CD setup, management and improvement: automate build and deployment pipelines and procedures;
- application infrastructure support including hardware, networks, OS, frameworks and related tools;
- test environments support;
- follow internal security operations procedures. Application and infrastructure audit compliance;
- deploy application releases, provide SL3 application on-call rota / weekend support;
- perform root cause analysis of production errors and resolve technical issues;
- cover monitoring and alerting needs.
- self motivated individual to perform tasks on his own
- certificate installations / renewal
- compliance related changes for application based on internal compliance requirements
Mandatory Skills:JIRA Structure
Linux
Shell Scripting
Site Reliability Engineer (SRE)
UNIX
Mandatory Skills Description:- 5+ years experience as a DevOps/SRE engineer or in a similar software engineering role;
- 5+ years experience with Linux diagnosis and support, deep bash knowledge;
- 5+ years experience with python coding;
- strong TCPIP;
- 5+ years experience with CI/CD: jenkins, build/test full flow support (support, development and improvement), groovy, artifactory;
- application release cycle experience: release engineer, SL3 support;
- IaC: ansible, git;
- docker experience;
- proficiency with monitoring;
- basic SQL;
- analytical thinking;
- good verbal and writing communication skills;
- proactive approach to identifying problems, performance bottlenecks, and areas for improvement;
- be independent in assigned tasks and projects, work as a team in responsibility area.

Roles & Responsibilities
Job Responsibilities:
Responsible for the management of Site Reliability Engineering, have hands-on knowledge on manage & troubleshot server, network and applications;
Responsible for the deployment and daily monitoring of the company's business systems to ensure the normal operation and emergency response;
Provide in-depth understanding of the operation and maintenance architecture, good at architecture design, performance optimization, platform security; Responsible for the improvement of the operation and maintenance team skills, to ensure the professional level of the operation and maintenance team.
Establish and improve standardized operation systems for DevOps team. Use a sound management strategies and security strategies to ensure the quality of operation and maintenance;
Job Requirements:
Familiar with automation deployment, proficient in how to build the most of popular monitoring system in the market. SVN/Git version control system and proficient in CICD configuration;
Hands-on knowledge in Nginx configuration, Load balancer (SLB) configuration. Familiar with Node.js running environment will be an advantage.
Skilled in managing Linux systems and security, with experience in operation and maintenance of large websites or web application platforms;
Understand common knowledge about the network, familiar with firewall, VPN, DHCP, DNS and other network technologies. Familiar with high availability/load balancing technology will be an advantage;
High sense of responsibility, strong ability to analyze and eliminate faults, good at learning at work, able to withstand work stress;
Understand the penetration test, have experience in safe operation and maintenance, and have working experience in Cloud platforms (AZURE, AWS or Google);
Working Environments: Hyper-Cloud, Cloudform/AWX, ELK, Zabbix, Jenkins/VSTS, GitLab etc. We build together, We learn together.
Candidate must possess at least Bachelor's Degree/Post Graduate Diploma/Professional Degree in Engineering (Computer/Telecommunication), Engineering (Electrical/Electronic), Computer Science/Information Technology or equivalent.
At least 3 years of working experience in the related field is required for senior position.
Preferably Senior Executive specialized in IT/Computer - Network/System/Database Admin or equivalent.
What we offer:
Proper training will provide to the senior position
Attractive rewards for long-term service staff
Energetic and friendly working environment (flexible working hours, quarterly events, staff birthday celebration and etc.)
Medical insurance

Roles & Responsibilities
Job Summary
We are looking for an experienced DevOps Platform Engineer with a strong background in Quality Assurance to work on Capital Market projects for a leading bank. The ideal candidate should have experience in infrastructure, automation, deployments, and test automation.

Mandatory Skill-set
Must have minimum 5 years of experience in relevant DevOps practices;
Must have experience in core technologies such as C#, and .NET development;
Strong knowledge of UNIX, SQL, Oracle, and Sybase;
Skilled in automation tools and scripting such as Python, Shell, PowerShell;
Exposure to DevOps tools such as GitLab, Jenkins, Ansible, CI/CD pipelines, and other tools like Control-M, Kafka, MQ, Confluence, Jira, Selenium, and Cucumber;
Experience in supporting capital market applications, particularly in Treasury and Fixed Income, with knowledge of financial products like FX, Credit, and Bonds;
Hands-on with Docker/Kubernetes and cloud platforms;
Desired Skill-set
Experience with Azure DevOps is a plus;
Experience in supporting banking and trading systems;
Knowledge of Domain-Driven Design and Microservices, with expertise in Spring Boot.
Responsibilities
Design and maintain tools to automate infrastructure, deployment, and quality assurance processes;
Collaborate with development teams to set up CI/CD pipelines and automate deployment/testing;
Oversee the transition of Orchestrade for Treasury into production;
Monitor system performance, resolve issues, and ensure security and compliance;
Enhance DevOps practices and develop effective QA strategies with automated testing;
Create test plans from requirements and promote early defect detection through effective testing methods;
Provide technical support, resolve issues, assist with data analysis, and document testing activities;
Stay current with the latest DevOps tools and technologies.

Should you be interested in this career opportunity, please send in your updated resume to apply@sciente.com at the earliest.

When you apply, you voluntarily consent to the disclosure, collection and use of your personal data for employment/recruitment and related purposes in accordance with the SCIENTE Group Privacy Policy, a copy of which is published at SCIENTE’s website (https://www.sciente.com/privacy-policy).

Confidentiality is assured, and only shortlisted candidates will be notified for interviews.

EA Licence No. 07C5639

Roles & Responsibilities
We are looking to speak to DevOps Engineers!

Responsibilities
Participate to the automation of the deployment solution.
Build, release, and deploy the platform on top of Jupyter Lab and Jupyter Hub;
Monitor the health of the platform and plan its capacity;
Secure the platform to prevent security breaches or unintended usage;
Tailor the platform to support evolving customer needs.
Monitor the results and quality of the different software solutions and projects implemented in the organisation
Ensure continuous improvement and maintenance of the CI-CD pipeline.

Requirements
Proficient in Linux, Docker, Kubernetes and Helm charts;
Good experience with shell-scripting;
Good experience with Git, ideally with Gitlab;
Good experience with Continuous Delivery, ideally with ArgoCD;
Good experience with Monitoring, ideally with Grafana;
Hands-on experience with Python or a similar programming language.

